HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 145
BY REPRESENTATIVE MARCELLE
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Carolyn Hill for her service to East Baton Rouge Parish
and the state of Louisiana
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Carolyn Hill for her service to East Baton Rouge Parish and the state of
3 Louisiana.
4 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Carolyn Hill for her civic mindedness and
5 leadership and to commend her for her service to East Baton Rouge Parish and the state of
6 Louisiana; and
7 WHEREAS, Ms. Hill is a native of Miami, Florida, who has proudly embraced
8 Louisiana as her home; she received a bachelor of social work from Southern University and
9 a master of social work with a concentration in policy and research from Louisiana State
10 University; and
11 WHEREAS, Ms. Hill is a nationally-certified school social worker, policy strategist,
12 and community leader with more than eighteen years of experience advancing educational
13 equity and promoting community empowerment; and
14 WHEREAS, Ms. Hill is a former elected member of the State Board of Elementary
15 and Secondary Education who represented the fourteen parishes within District 8 and
16 became one of the youngest individuals ever elected to the board; and
17 WHEREAS, Ms. Hill previously served as chair of the East Baton Rouge Democratic
18 Parish Executive Committee, where she provided leadership in civic engagement, political
19 strategy, and community mobilization; and
