3 development, leadership development, and community engagement; and
4 WHEREAS, Ms. Hill currently holds the Miss Louisiana for America title, and her
5 platform is centered on human trafficking awareness and advocacy; she is committed to
6 policy reform and victim protection; and
7 WHEREAS, Ms. Hill is actively engaged in numerous civic and philanthropic
8 initiatives; she is a member of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Incorporated, and continues to
9 serve in leadership roles that advance community connection and service; and
10 WHEREAS, Ms. Hill is currently pursuing a juris master degree and expanding her
11 expertise at the intersection of law, policy, and leadership; she is truly most deserving of the
12 highest recognition for her outstanding achievements and service to the community.
13 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
14 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Carolyn Hill for her service to East Baton
15 Rouge Parish and the state of Louisiana and does hereby extend sincere wishes that she
16 remain prosperous in all of her endeavors.
